---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Integration Testing with JUnit & Spring Boot Test - SYP">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a href="/syp-overview" class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to SYP Overview
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white">
                    Integration Testing with JUnit & Spring Boot Test
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    Comprehensive testing strategy: unit tests with mocking, integration tests with Spring context, and fixtures for test data
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        Testing is how we ensure code works before it reaches production. I implemented a comprehensive testing strategy: 
                        unit tests with Mockito for individual methods, integration tests using Spring Boot Test context, and test fixtures 
                        for consistent test data. This gives confidence that features work and prevents regressions.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Learning Journey</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">🧪 Challenge: Test Types</h3>
                            <p>
                                Not all tests are equal. Unit tests verify individual methods. Integration tests verify the whole stack 
                                (database, services, controllers). Learned when to use each for optimal coverage and speed.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">🎭 Challenge: Mocking Dependencies</h3>
                            <p>
                                Services depend on DAOs, email, etc. Can't test these with real implementations (too slow, external 
                                dependencies). Learned Mockito to create mock objects for controlled testing.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">📊 Challenge: Consistent Test Data</h3>
                            <p>
                                Tests need predictable data. Created fixtures (builder objects) to consistently create test users, items, 
                                and bids. Prevents random failures from inconsistent test data.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">⚡ Challenge: Test Speed</h3>
                            <p>
                                Integration tests with database are slower. Use unit tests for fast feedback, integration tests for critical 
                                paths. Balanced testing pyramid.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">✅ Key Learning</h3>
                            <p>
                                Good tests catch bugs early, enable refactoring with confidence, and document expected behavior. Testing 
                                is an investment in code quality.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Key Implementation</h2>
                    
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Unit Test with Mockito</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// SponsorServiceImplTest.java - Unit Test
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)  // JUnit 5 with Mockito
public class SponsorServiceImplTest {
    
    @Mock
    private SponsorDao sponsorDao;
    
    @InjectMocks
    private SponsorServiceImpl sponsorService;

    @Test
    void testSaveValid() {
        // Arrange
        SponsorDto dto = new SponsorDto(null, "New Sponsor", "Contact");
        Sponsor entity = new Sponsor(1L, "New Sponsor", "Contact");
        
        when(sponsorDao.findByName("New Sponsor")).thenReturn(Optional.empty());
        when(sponsorDao.save(any(Sponsor.class))).thenReturn(entity);

        // Act
        SponsorDto result = sponsorService.save(dto);

        // Assert
        assertNotNull(result);
        assertEquals(1L, result.getId());
        assertEquals("New Sponsor", result.getName());
        
        verify(sponsorDao, times(1)).save(any(Sponsor.class));
    }

    @Test
    void testSaveDuplicate() {
        // Arrange
        SponsorDto dto = new SponsorDto(null, "Existing", "Contact");
        Sponsor existing = new Sponsor(5L, "Existing", "Contact");
        
        when(sponsorDao.findByName("Existing")).thenReturn(Optional.of(existing));

        // Act & Assert
        assertThrows(SponsorAlreadyExistsException.class, () -> {
            sponsorService.save(dto);
        });
        
        verify(sponsorDao, never()).save(any());
    }

    @Test
    void testGetPaginatedWithPagination() {
        // Arrange
        Sponsor sponsor1 = new Sponsor(1L, "A", "Contact");
        Sponsor sponsor2 = new Sponsor(2L, "B", "Contact");
        Page<Sponsor> page = new PageImpl<>(List.of(sponsor1, sponsor2));
        
        when(sponsorDao.findAll(any(Pageable.class))).thenReturn(page);

        // Act
        Page<SponsorDto> result = sponsorService.getSponsorsDtoPaginated(0, 10, "name", "ASC");

        // Assert
        assertEquals(2, result.getContent().size());
        verify(sponsorDao, times(1)).findAll(any(Pageable.class));
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Unit tests use @Mock to create fake DAOs. @InjectMocks injects mocks into service. Fast and isolated.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Integration Test with Spring Boot Test</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// ItemServiceIntegrationTest.java
@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)
@Transactional  // Rollback after each test
public class ItemServiceIntegrationTest {
    
    @Autowired
    private ItemService itemService;
    
    @Autowired
    private UserRepository userRepository;
    
    @Autowired
    private ItemRepository itemRepository;
    
    private TestFixture fixture;

    @BeforeEach
    void setup() {
        fixture = new TestFixture(userRepository, itemRepository);
        fixture.clearAll();
    }

    @Test
    void testPlaceBidSuccess() {
        // Arrange - Use fixtures for consistent data
        User bidder = fixture.createUser("bidder@example.com");
        Item item = fixture.createItem("Test Item", item -> {
            item.setCurrentBid(BigDecimal.valueOf(50));
        });

        BidDto bidDto = new BidDto();
        bidDto.setItemId(item.getId());
        bidDto.setAmount(BigDecimal.valueOf(75));
        bidDto.setUserId(bidder.getId());

        // Act
        BidDto result = itemService.placeBid(bidDto);

        // Assert
        assertNotNull(result);
        assertEquals(BigDecimal.valueOf(75), result.getAmount());
        
        // Verify in database
        Item updatedItem = itemRepository.findById(item.getId()).orElseThrow();
        assertEquals(BigDecimal.valueOf(75), updatedItem.getCurrentBid());
    }

    @Test
    void testPlaceBidTooLow() {
        // Arrange
        User bidder = fixture.createUser("bidder@example.com");
        Item item = fixture.createItem("Test Item", item -> {
            item.setCurrentBid(BigDecimal.valueOf(100));
        });

        BidDto bidDto = new BidDto();
        bidDto.setItemId(item.getId());
        bidDto.setAmount(BigDecimal.valueOf(50));  // Lower than current
        bidDto.setUserId(bidder.getId());

        // Act & Assert
        assertThrows(IntendedException.class, () -> {
            itemService.placeBid(bidDto);
        });
    }

    @Test
    void testGetItemsPaginated() {
        // Arrange - Create multiple items
        for (int i = 0; i < 25; i++) {
            fixture.createItem("Item " + i);
        }

        // Act
        Page<ItemDto> page1 = itemService.getItemsDtoPaginated(0, 10, "name", "ASC");
        Page<ItemDto> page2 = itemService.getItemsDtoPaginated(1, 10, "name", "ASC");

        // Assert
        assertEquals(10, page1.getContent().size());
        assertEquals(10, page2.getContent().size());
        assertEquals(25, page1.getTotalElements());
        assertEquals(3, page1.getTotalPages());
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Integration tests load full Spring context. @Transactional rolls back each test for isolation. 
                            Tests the entire stack with real database.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Test Fixtures for Consistent Data</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// TestFixture.java - Reusable Test Data Builder
public class TestFixture {
    private final UserRepository userRepository;
    private final ItemRepository itemRepository;
    private int userCounter = 1;
    private int itemCounter = 1;

    public User createUser(String email) {
        return createUser(email, user -> {});
    }

    public User createUser(String email, Consumer<User> modifier) {
        User user = new User();
        user.setEmail(email);
        user.setFirstName("Test");
        user.setLastName("User" + userCounter++);
        user.setPasswordHash("hashedpassword");
        
        modifier.accept(user);
        
        return userRepository.save(user);
    }

    public Item createItem(String name) {
        return createItem(name, item -> {});
    }

    public Item createItem(String name, Consumer<Item> modifier) {
        Item item = new Item();
        item.setName(name);
        item.setDescription("Test item " + itemCounter);
        item.setCreatedBy(createUser("seller" + itemCounter + "@example.com"));
        item.setCurrentBid(BigDecimal.ZERO);
        item.setStatus(new Status(2L, "ACTIVE"));  // ACTIVE status
        
        modifier.accept(item);
        
        return itemRepository.save(item);
    }

    public void clearAll() {
        itemRepository.deleteAll();
        userRepository.deleteAll();
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Fixtures create test data with sensible defaults. Consumer functions allow customization. 
                            Reduces test boilerplate and improves readability.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Testing Strategy</h2>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">🚀 Unit Tests (Fast)</h3>
                            <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                                <li>• Test individual methods</li>
                                <li>• Mock all dependencies</li>
                                <li>• Run in seconds</li>
                                <li>• Most tests should be here</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">🔗 Integration Tests (Slower)</h3>
                            <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                                <li>• Test service + database</li>
                                <li>• Full Spring context</li>
                                <li>• Run in seconds</li>
                                <li>• Critical paths only</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">🌐 E2E Tests (Slowest)</h3>
                            <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                                <li>• Test full API endpoints</li>
                                <li>• TestRestTemplate</li>
                                <li>• Run in minutes</li>
                                <li>• Smoke tests only</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">📊 Testing Pyramid</h3>
                            <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                                <li>• Many unit tests (base)</li>
                                <li>• Some integration tests</li>
                                <li>• Few E2E tests (top)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Technology Stack</h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {['JUnit 5', 'Mockito', 'Spring Boot Test', '@SpringBootTest', 'TestFixture', '@Transactional', 'Page<T>'].map((tech) => (
                            <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                {tech}
                            </span>
                        ))}
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Results & Impact</h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Fast Feedback:</strong> Unit tests run in seconds, catch bugs immediately</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Confidence in Refactoring:</strong> Tests ensure changes don't break existing behavior</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Living Documentation:</strong> Tests show how code is supposed to be used</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Reduced Manual Testing:</strong> Automated tests catch regressions early</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
